    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Sir F.
                        Bruce</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir Frederick:</hi> I find, on turning to our
                    files, that on the 22d Instant instructions were addressed to Mr. Adams, in
                    which he was requested to impart to Earl Russell the sense entertained by the
                    government and people of the United States of the manifestations of sympathy and
                    condolence conveyed to us in the despatches addressed by Earl Russell to you on
                    the 28th of April and 6th instant, respectively.</p>
                <p>Believe me to be, my dear sir, very faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir Frederick W. A. Bruce,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
